cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new stochastic version of the softmax classifier that uses dropout probabilities to adaptively drop non-target classes. The paper focuses on classification tasks and uses variational inference to learn the dropout rates for each instance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
